MKrvy0Kdc-T_PTyf1WmUJg.text: Solid coffee joint, with a staff that cares about coffee and cares enough to explain and help you make good choices. Their drip is excellent, done slowly and with care. As others have mentioned, it's a welcome respite from the nearby Orchard Towers crowd, and a nice alternative to the coffee beans and terrible Starbucks coffee. Americans be warned - no filtered coffee available.

5OVTrwewAplCMTz8H2K1-w.text: Great coffee on Orchard Rd..if Starbucks is getting 4stars then there are not enough here for this one.

X2fLnM2_7fEf5rcobKk9yA.text: Ambitious place that challenges big-name neighbours (Starbucks, Coffee Bean, etc) and sells more than coffee and tea: salads, semi-serious b'fasts (eg. waffles with fresh fruits, eggs benedict), as well as 4 kinds of beer and food (eg. linguine with clams, smoked joint, deep fried pork cubes). May not attract many customers from Orchard Towers next door; those may prefer mee sua in the basement or greasy quesadillas with mojitos at Señor Taco anyway.

photos.caption: Photo of Jewel Coffee - Singapore, Singapore

-GFpoEk6wLepZXfuv_nUyw.text: Cute place to get some work done. Pretty quiet with some chill music on a lazy Monday Labour Day. There's free wi-fi with facebook check-in or filling out a form (pretty straightforward once you connect). Too bad the outlets were few and far between though. The internet speed was pretty decent although it started out a bit slow. The A/C was wayyy too cold though, so unfortunately I had to bounce after about 2 hrs. My hairs were standing on end!

cWYgTvuL8kZDyYLWJRGfsA.text: Had great coffee from here almost everyday. Usually ordered with Sumatran beans for a more local flavor. Really really good

s3FD9Ihmehu_wstOqgA4oQ.text: Best coffee in Orchard, on a quiet side street. Good seating options, nice place to chill. Looks pricey, but cups are gigantic!

hdNSWVaaKUBpLYe3E_JwEg.text: Great coffee with many variations of the latte -- piccolo, Gibraltar, cappuccino etc. also variants of drip/brew coffee. Watch out -- the latte is a huge cup of coffee. Too milky for me. Gibraltar hits just the right spot. They don't offer decaf like many other proper cafes, most frustratingly. Eggs and toast at $6, with butter and jam, is an affordable option compared to $16 similar breakfasts down Orchard Road. Bonus points to Jewel for offering vegemite if you prefer it.

m8TAq29YrsB4kLIRe9Qtqw.text: Ordered a flat white ($6) and pain au chocolate ($3) for breakfast before my Japanese class at Delfi Orchard. The coffee was unlike anything I've ever tasted and was brilliant. Smooth yet strong, I savoured every single drop of it. It went well with the pastry although the latter was just a tad too sweet.

p1ZP5prH5UmrwZlBTdwBBQ.text: They are one of the few speciality coffee shops in the area.  Very fresh and all beans have dates.  They don't have full body kind, but that's alright other beans are also good.Thanks for opening here.  You are awesome!こちらでは少ないスペシャリティコーヒーのお店です。ここで焼いているわけではありませんが、ストレートコーヒーをちゃんと焼いた日付を記して販売しています。日本のように苦めの焼き方はしてませんが、十分美味しいです。お値段もお手頃で、いいお店ですね。2015/11
